<br>
I believe, firmly, that there is NO &quot;One Right True Way&quot;. Everyone has their own path to walk, and no one answer is universally correct for all people. Everyone lives under different circumstances. My life is RADICALLY different than, say a citizen of Zaire. How then could we have the SAME religious needs and choices? We can't.<br>
<br>
I have no issue with someone being highly religious as a devout christian, and chosing to live their life by the tenets of that religion. Indeed, I would applaud them for having a moral compass and sticking to it. What I object to is if that person expects ME to follow the same tenets, when I don't follow the same religion.<br>
<br>
That's the big thing I've been arguing here. Political figures, of any religion whatsoever, trying to make laws or policy decisions based on their beliefs is by definition unfair and oppressive to anyone else who happens to believe differently. It's just as wrong for christian political figures to make public policy based on Christian moral values as it would be for a Hindu politician outlawing the eating of Beef, a Jewish one outlawing Pork, or a Wiccan one demanding you call circle.<br>
<br>
-Arlos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=smeegolthebadtank>smeegolthebadtank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/03 1:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is interesting...</span><hr size=1>  Arlos you know that talking to some people is like talking to a brick wall. I see your points and I agree 100% with you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trindle>Trindle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1124<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/03 4:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is interesting...</span><hr size=1> I still like the idea of daily orgies though. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=durck>Durck</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Squirrel</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/03 6:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.satx.rr.com/rfaulkner/images/DURCKPIC.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign