Good definition of Government. Maybe I didn't state my point clearly enough. When the Government makes laws deciding what is wrong and good and not good, it does *NOT* have to make them based on Christian Morality, or indeed, *ANY* religious morality. Got it now?<br>
<br>
Indeed, BY making those decisions based on ONE specific moral code, you are oppressing every single other inhabitant who happens to follow a DIFFERENT religion's moral code.  <br>
<br>
To go back to an earlier example: Christian Morals says &quot;Drugs are BAD!&quot;. They have thus been made illegal by politicians letting their religious beliefs shape their public policy making. Now, you have Person X, a native american, who's religious choice is to attempt to follow the shamanistic path of his ancestors. Part of some of those religions is vision and dream questing, using Peyote as an aid. However, Peyote is ILLEGAL in this country. Does his using Peyote in ceremony have any impact whatsoever on anyone other than himself? Not in any way, shape, or form. Haven't those laws based on Christian Morality now extremely infringed upon that person's basic right to practice his religion as it had been done for hundreds of years? Why yes, yes it has. <br>
<br>
You see where I'm coming from now?<br>
<br>
